gomodel:SYNGO_3099  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Nrx3-C1ql2/3 Signaling Recruits KARs in Cultured Hippocampal Neurons\"\n- \"To define the roles for Nrx3-C1ql2/3 interactions in organizing KAR-containing synapses, we expressed Nrx3β+SS525b together with C1ql2 and C1ql3 (C1ql2+3) on the surface of HEK293 cells and cocultured them with C1ql2/3 null hippocampal neurons. We found that endogenous GluK2/3, as well as neuroligin 1 (NL1, a receptor that binds to all Nrx isoforms) and PSD95, accumulated in hippocampal neurons contacting HEK293 cells (Figure 5A). \". Experimental description: - Dissociated neurons were from mice.\nlacking a corresponding gene to confirm antibody specificity. (Legend Fig. 1A, p. 754)\n- Overexpressed C1QL2_MOUSE, Complement C1q-like protein 2, C1ql2, C1q/TNF-related protein 10 is of rat species: \"A series of constructs for Mus musculus C1ql2 proteins (NP_997116) and C1ql3 proteins (NP_694795) with\nan N-terminal or a C-terminal hemagglutinin (HA)-tag were amplified by PCR\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" ;
        dc:date           "2018-04-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3099" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

